ccepted.\",\n    \"CookieJar.set_cookie_if_ok\": \"Store the given cookie only if the current policy says it is acceptable for the given request.\",\n    \"CookieJar.set_policy\": \"Replace the cookie policy of the underlying jar with the given pol policy object.\",\n    \"WrappedRequest.add_unredirected_header\": \"Append a header with the given name and value to the wrapped request headers; Scrapy does not track redirect-only headers separately.\",\n    \"WrappedRequest.full_url\": \"The full URL of the wrapped request, mirroring get_full_url for property-style access.\",\n    \"WrappedRequest.get_full_url\": \"Return the complete URL of the wrapped Scrapy request.\",\n    \"WrappedRequest.get_header\": \"Return the first value of the header with the given name decoded to text, or the provided default when the header is absent.\",\n    \"WrappedRequest.get_host\": \"Return the network location (host and optional port) of the wrapped request URL.\",\n    \"WrappedRequest.get_type\": \"Return the scheme of the wrapped request URL, such as http or https.\",\n    \"WrappedRequest.has_header\": \"Return True when a header with the given name is present on the wrapped request.\",\n    \"WrappedRequest.header_items\": \"Return the wrapped request headers as a list of (header name, list of decoded values) tuples.\",\n    \"WrappedRequest.host\": \"The network location of the wrapped request URL, exposed as a property for the stdlib cookie interface.\",\n    \"WrappedRequest.origin_req_host\": \"The hostname of the wrapped request URL, used by cookie policies to decide third-party cookie handling.\",\n    \"WrappedRequest.type\": \"The URL scheme of the wrapped request, exposed as a property for the stdlib cookie interface.\",\n    \"WrappedRequest.unverifiable\": \"Whether the wrapped request is unverifiable per RFC 2965, exposed as a property over is_unverifiable.\",\n    \"WrappedResponse\": \"Wraps a Scrapy Response so it exposes the message-like interface that http.cookiejar expects when extracting cookies.\",\n    \"WrappedResponse.get_all\": \"Return every value of the response header with the given name decoded to text; default is accepted for interface compatibility but unused.\",\n    \"WrappedResponse.info\": \"Return this wrapper itself, satisfying the stdlib API that expects an object with header accessors.\",\n    \"_DummyLock.acquire\": \"No-op lock acquisition; Scrapy crawls are single-threaded here so no real locking is needed.\",\n    \"_DummyLock.release\": \"No-op lock release matching the no-op acquire of this stand-in lock.\"\n  }\n}\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null,"userModified":false}}
1781268380.149	{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-fable-5","id":"msg_01GVayJTx1edz4GrG8fGSrMA","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01V4vLLngjGWQcd4DUdMM3w7","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/home/svankina/src/local_agents/results/experiments/showcase-fanout/2026-06-12-S-02-timing-probe/workers/item-02-attempt-1/response.json","content":"{\n  \"docstrings\": {\n    \"DummyStatsCollector\": \"Stats collector that discards every recorded value, useful to disable stats collection while keeping the collector API available.\",\n    \"DummyStatsCollector.get_value\": \"Return the provided default for any key since nothing is stored; the spider argument is accepted only for backward compatibility.\",\n    \"DummyStatsCollector.inc_value\": \"Ignore the increment request; key, count, start and spider are all discarded by this collector.\",\n    \"DummyStatsCollector.max_value\": \"Ignore the request to track the maximum value for key; spider is accepted only for backward compatibility.\",\n    \"DummyStatsCollector.min_value\": \"Ignore the request to track the minimum value for key; spider is accepted only for backward compatibility.\",\n    \"DummyStatsCollector.set_stats\": \"Ignore the given stats mapping entirely; spider is accepted only for backward compatibility.\",\n    \"DummyStatsCollector.set_value\": \"Ignore the request to store value under key; spider is accepted only for backward compatibility.\",\n    \"MemoryStatsCollector\": \"Stats collector that keeps the final stats of each closed spider in memory, keyed by spider name in the spider_stats mapping.\",\n    \"StatsCollector\": \"Base stats collector that stores crawl statistics in an in-memory mapping and optionally dumps them to the log when the spider closes.\",\n    \"StatsCollector.clear_stats\": \"Remove every stored stat; the spider argument is deprecated and accepted only for backward compatibility.\",\n    \"StatsCollector.close_spider\": \"Handle spider closure for the given reason, dumping the collected stats to the log when STATS_DUMP is enabled and persisting them.\",\n    \"StatsCollector.get_stats\": \"Return the mapping with all stats currently collected; the spider argument is deprecated and accepted only for backward compatibility.\",\n    \"StatsCollector.get_value\": \"Return the stat stored under key, or the given default when the key is missing; spider is accepted only for backward compatibility.\",\n    \"StatsCollector.inc_value\": \"Increase the stat stored under key by count, initializing it to start when missing; spider is accepted only for backward compatibility.\",\n    \"StatsCollector.max_value\": \"Store value under key only when it is greater than the value already recorded; spider is accepted only for backward compatibility.\",\n    \"StatsCollector.min_value\": \"Store value under key only when it is smaller than the value already recorded; spider is accepted only for backward compatibility.\",\n    \"StatsCollector.open_spider\": \"Hook called when a spider is opened; the base implementation does nothing and spider is accepted only for backward compatibility.\",\n    \"StatsCollector.set_stats\": \"Replace the whole stats mapping with the given stats dictionary; spider is accepted only for backward compatibility.\",\n    \"StatsCollector.set_value\": \"Store value under key, overwriting any previous stat; spider is accepted only for backward compatibility.\"\n  }\n}\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":11302,"cache_read_input_tokens":66537,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":11302},"output_tokens":4,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"455c3339-708e-46be-b783-7b0d8d3ce5a3","uuid":"5096e841-c502-431e-a2e4-69f9fa018e2e","r